            "answer_text": "What is the reason that Bhojpuri is considered as a low class language? It is about perception, isn\u2019t it? Bhojpuri is mainly spoken in Northern Bihar and Eastern UP(in India) and these regions are not economically strong. People from these areas often go out and work as labourer elsewhere. This may have created a perception that Bhojpuri is a low class language. As far as the languages spoken as mother tongue goes, Bhojpuri is above Punjabi and Malayalam.  Also, Lalu Prasad Yadav ruined it :P List of languages by number of native speakers in India - Wikipedia ",
